### Issue description

I hope to put a TableLayoutPanel in a Form and turn on AutoScroll to make sure have ability to display every controls in it, one of its inner control is changing height (such as a AutoSized FlowLayoutTable will change its height when inner control rearranged due to width's change), the issue is that outside TableLayoutPanel doesn't shrink with inner FlowLayoutPanel's height reducing.

### Steps to reproduce

Scenario 1:
Dock a TableLayoutPanel with {AutoScroll=true, AutoSize=true, AutoSizeMode=GrowAndShrink and one AutoSize row} to a form, dock a FlowLayoutPanel with {AutoSize=true and AutoSizeMode=GrowAndShrink} to the only row of TableLayoutPanel. TableLayoutPanel and FLowLayoutPanel don't shrink although they have enough space to display all inner controls.
``` csharp
    public Form1()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        var tableLayoutPanel = new TableLayoutPanel
        {
            AutoScroll = true,
            AutoSize = true,
            Dock = DockStyle.Fill,
            AutoSizeMode = AutoSizeMode.GrowAndShrink,
            RowCount = 0,
            BackColor = Color.Blue,
            CellBorderStyle = TableLayoutPanelCellBorderStyle.Single
        };

        tableLayoutPanel.RowStyles.Clear();
        tableLayoutPanel.RowStyles.Add(new RowStyle(SizeType.AutoSize));
        tableLayoutPanel.RowCount++;

        var flowLayoutPanel = new FlowLayoutPanel()
        {
            AutoSize = true,
            AutoSizeMode = AutoSizeMode.GrowAndShrink,
            Margin = new Padding(20),
            BackColor = Color.Red,
            Dock = DockStyle.Fill,
        };

        for (var index = 0; index < 100; index++)
        {
            flowLayoutPanel.Controls.Add(new Button()
            {
                Text = index.ToString()
            });
        }

        tableLayoutPanel.Controls.Add(flowLayoutPanel, 0, 0);
        this.Controls.Add(tableLayoutPanel);
    }
```
